<title>UK: Asahi Bank details 100 bln yen issue.</title>
<headline>Asahi Bank details 100 bln yen issue.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following convertible preference share issue was announced by joint lead managers Goldman Sachs International, Nikko Europe Plc and Asahi Finance (UK) Ltd.</p>
<p> BORROWER   AB INTERNATIONAL CAYMAN TRUST</p>
<p> AMT    100 BLN YEN   DIVIDEND   0.75	MATURITY    01.AUG.07</p>
<p> TYPE   PREF SHARE    ISS PRICE  2.0 MLN   PAY DATE    =</p>
<p> FULL FEES  2.5	 LISTING    LUX	 PREMIUM     2.5</p>
<p> MOODY/S&amp;P  BAA1/BBB</p>
<p> NOTES	CONVERTIBLE INTO PREFERNCE SHARES OF THE ASAHI</p>
<p>		BANK LTD.</p>
<p>		CALLABLE FROM 07.AUG.02 SUBJECT TO 130 PCT RULE</p>
<p>		CONVERTIBLE FROM 01.OCT.97 UNTIL 31.JUL.07</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7658</p>
